author: The Denver Post
title: Matt Janning waived by Denver Nuggets; signs with Israeli team
text:
Matt Janning waived by Denver Nuggets; signs with Israeli team 6-foot-4, 198-pound guard played in two preseason games with Denver NBA standings 
The Denver Nuggets have waived Matt Janning, the team announced Thursday. 
The 6-foot-4, 198-pound guard played in two preseason games with the team, averaging 1.0 points and 4.6 minutes. 
Janning, 27, signed with Hapoel Jerusalem B.C. in the Israel Premier League Thursday. 
"Big thanks to everyone involved with the @Nuggets organization for the great opportunity. Wishing them the best this year!" Janning tweeted . 
With the move, Denver's roster is reduced to 18 players. Advertisement
